data.title: The world pays homage to Steve Jobs
data.meta_description: Makeshift memorials around the globe as the world reacts to the passing of an extraordinary life
data.text:
Flowers and other mementos left at Apple's Fifth Avenue store in New York City.

Apples and candles adorn a makeshift memorial for Steve Jobs at the Apple headquarters on October 5, 2011 in Cupertino, California.

A man places a flower bouquet paying tribute to Apple co-founder Steve Jobs outside an Apple store in Tokyo on October 6, 2011.

Mario Spinetti sits outside the Apple Store on West 66th Street after hearing of the death of Steve Jobs, founder and former CEO of Apple

Apples with messages paying tribute to Apple co-founder Steve Jobs outside an Apple store in Tokyo on October 6, 2011. The passing of Steve Jobs left people around the world "iSad" on October 6, with countless mourners typing out their grief on the handheld Apple gadgets that have transformed modern life. AFP PHOTO / Yoshikazu TSUNO (Photo credit should read YOSHIKAZU TSUNO/AFP/Getty Images)

Candles, flowers, and an iPhone with Steve Jobs photo displayed, are seen in remembrance of Steve Jobs, founder and former CEO of Apple Inc, outside the Apple Store at Broadway and West 67th Street on October 5, 2011 in New York City.

Post-it notes cover the clear glass at the Apple Store at Broadway and 67th Street in New York.

Candles illuminate a memorial to Apple co-founder Steve Jobs, Thursday, Oct. 6, 2011 in front of an Apple store in New York.

A person takes a photograph with an iPhone of an In Memoriam photo of Steve Jobs, who founded and ran Apple, on display in an Apple store in Prague, Czech Republic, Thursday Oct. 6, 2011.

Fresh apples, flowers and a large poster of Steve Jobs are placed outside an Apple retail store in Beijing, China, Thursday, Oct. 6, 2011.

An iMac computer shows the image of Apple co-founder Steve Jobs at an electronic shop in Hong Kong, Thursday, Oct. 6, 2011.

A woman in Frankfurt, Germany lays flowers outside of an Apple store, Thursday Oct. 6, 2011.

Chinese exchange students from nearby De Anza College use candles to create the Apple logo and Steve Jobs' last name in Chinese characters at a makeshift memorial for Steve Jobs at the Apple headquarters on October 5, 2011 in Cupertino, California.

Flags fly at half staff following the death of Steve Jobs at the Apple headquarters on October 5, 2011 in Cupertino, California.

People mourn Apple co-founder Steve Jobs at an Apple store at Sanlitun Village on October 06, 2011 in Beijing,

People mourn Apple co-founder Steve Jobs at an Apple store on October 06, 2011 in Shanghai, China.

Someone spray painted a message to Steve Jobs on Apple's 5th Avenue store in New York City. Also known as the Cube, the glass structure is undergoing renovations and a wooden structure covers the glass. Workers later removed the graffiti.
